body:
Hello @qwhelan! Thanks for submitting the PR.

 - There are no PEP8 issues in the file [`asv_bench/benchmarks/groupby.py`](https://github.com/qwhelan/pandas/blob/d3fa9d67670b022750ed9a1e248c52c25d3a3339/asv_bench/benchmarks/groupby.py) !

I'm not sure the benchmark is to blame here. I think this is more of a byproduct of agg giving inconsistent results, i.e.:

```python
df.groupby('key1').agg(sum)  
```

would yield something different than

```python
df.groupby('key1').agg([sum])
```

If you search there should be an open issue about this. Would rather fix that than change the benchmark, though `setup_cache` change itself would be OK
I believe this mostly been fixed in master

My point is that the aggregations should not be applied to the object column. It only seems to do that when supplying an iterable of functions, whereas applying individually does the right thing
@WillAyd Okay, I can add separate benchmarks for the single function case but the intent of the existing benchmark seems to be to compare multiple aggregation performance on numeric data.
